mistake because by recapturing with)} bxc6 {∞ , Black gains strong control of the center.}) (11. O-O $6 {would be an inaccuracy because Black can continue with} cxd5 12. cxd5 b5 $1 {∞ when} 13. Bxb5 {fails due to all the captures on e4 followed by ...Qb6+ regaining the bishop.}) 11... cxd5 12. cxd5 $1 (12. exd5 $6 e6 13. dxe6 Bxe6 {∞ In this position, White would be better if the pawn were on e4 instead of c4.}) 12... Qa5 {This was the move played by Svidler in Ding-Svidler 2018.} 13. O-O Bd7 {[%cal Gf8c8,Gb7b5] Black wants to continue with ...Rfc8 and b7-b5.} 14. e5 $1 {[%cal Rc5d7] White uses the fact that Black's knight cannot retreat on d7.} Ne8 15. Bd4 $14 {[%cal Gd1d2,Gf1d1] We can continue with Qd2-Rfd1 and it's clear that Black is suffering.} *

