{Black supports their knight and wants to develop their bishop to b7.} (12... Nfd7 $6 13. h4 $1 {followed by h4-h5.}) 13. Qc2 Bb7 14. O-O-O Nfd7 (14... Qe8 {This move has been played against me by the solid Croatian GM Bogdan Lalic in 2019, but after} 15. h4 $1 {± White is again very fast in creating an attack on the kingside.}) 15. h4 $1 {[%cal Gh4h5] White is ready to initiate a kingside attack. The idea is h4-h5.} Bxc3 {Capitalizing on White being unable to recapture with the queen due to the pawn on e4.} (15... Qe7 16. h5 {± Black's king is too weak and White has a serious advantage.}) 16. bxc3 {White still aims to play h5.} e5 {This is Black's best continuation.} 17. f5 {White's attack comes very quickly.} *

