pawn but not the d-pawn.} (18. Be2 $2 {In all the games that reached this position, White played this move, which turned out to be a serious tactical mistake.} Bxc3 19. Qxc3 Qxc3+ 20. bxc3 Nxd5 $1 {⩱ And, in the case of} 21. exd5 {, the bishop on e3 is undefended.}) 18... Qxf3 19. h5 $16 {[%cal Ge1f1] Black has an extra pawn, but otherwise, their position is lost. White is ready to continue with Ref1 and has a decisive attack.} *

