. Now, Black will have no counterplay on the queenside, while White can quickly launch an attack on the kingside.} 14. h4 {+-}) 14. Bc4 $16 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Gc4d5,Gh2h4,Gh4h5] White exerts strong pressure on the d5-square, making it challenging for Black to support the knight effectively. We can proceed with h4-h5 or, in some cases, exchange with Bxd5 followed by ...cxd5 and h4-h5. Black is left with little-to-no counterplay.} *

