2+ {, as it can only help us to play} 18. Kf2 {.}) 17... f6 {According to the engine, this is Black's best continuation. It may look strange, but after you check the 17...[N4xd5] sideline, you will understand this move better.} (17... Nc2+ $2 18. Kf2 {±}) (17... N4xd5 $4 18. Nxd5 Nxd5 19. Rxd5 Qxd5 20. Qf6#) 18. g4 Bc2 19. Rd2 Rf7 $1 {[%cal Gf7h7] Black wants to continue with ...Rxh7.} 20. Rhh2 $3 {[%cal Gd2h2] So that after ...Rxh7 our rook will be defended.} Rxh7 21. Qe3 {Now the game gets quite forced.} Bg6 22. d6 Rxh2 $1 23. Rxh2+ Kg7 24. Qh6+ Kf7 25. Rd2 {Intending f2-f4 next, so Black needs to hurry up in exchanging the queens.} Qh8 $1 26. Qxh8 Rxh8 27. Nh3 $14 {[%cal Gf3f4] White will continue with f2-f4. We have an extra pawn, but according to the engine, Black has some compensation. Still, they will need to find many precise moves, and White has excellent winning chances, especially in a practical game.} *

