king Black's pawn on h6.} Be6 {Black creates counterplay against the c4-pawn.} 11. Be2 {A necessary developing move because we need to be ready for castle.} Ne5 {[%csl Rc4] Black attacks our c4-pawn.} 12. b3 c6 {This move has been played in the only three games that have reached this position.} 13. O-O Re8 (13... d5 $2 {Black is not ready for the d6-d5 break.} 14. Bd4 Qc7 15. f4 {±}) 14. Qe1 $14 {[%csl Rd6][%cal Ga1d1] Our idea is to place a rook on d1 so that it will be very difficult for Black to play d6-d5. Without d6-d5, Black's position is simply worse.} *

