 9. Nxd4 exd4 10. Qxd4 h6 11. Bxf6 (11. Bh4 $4 {It's always important to be careful when our queen is on d4, as Black may have some discovering knight jumps in mind.} g5 12. Bg3 Nxe4 $1 {-+}) 11... Bxf6 12. Qd2 $14 {The fact that the engine prefers 8...Nd4 over 8...Ne7 doesn't mean that Black is equalizing, but rather that 8...Ne7 is really bad. In fact, here Black has some compensation for the missing pawn, but certainly not full compensation. White can continue with Bd3 and O-O, and while the game might end in a draw against an engine, against a human opponent, Black will likely face significant difficulties.} *

