ong castle and can then start to launch his own kingside play with g4-h4.} 9. Qd2 {Black's only plan in this position is to play f7-f5. To prepare for this, they are usually starting with Ne8.} Ne8 10. O-O-O f5 $2 {It is very bad if White's bishop is still on g5.} 11. exf5 gxf5 (11... Rxf5 $6 12. h4 {+- followed by h5 and Ng3.}) 12. g4 $1 (12. g4 {We are immediately opening some lines on the kingside. For example,} fxg4 13. fxg4 Bxg4 14. Rg1 {± .}) *

