ve, as it allows us to continue with} 12. d5 Ne7 13. c6 {+- where Black is completely suffocated.}) 12. Nf2 $1 {[%csl Gf2] This is a good square for our knight.} Re8 13. Bg5 $16 (13. Bg5 {Black is not in time to execute their plan because after} dxc5 14. Rxc5 Bf8 {, White is winning with} 15. Rxc6 Bxc6 16. e5 {. If Black remains passive, we can continue with h2-h4, threatening h4-h5. If Black responds with h4-h5, we can open up the kingside by playing g2-g4.}) *

